A vehicle is in linear motion. The scalar velocity as a function of time is given by

\begin{equation*}
v(t) = b_0t^2 -\,a_0t\ ,
\end{equation*}

where $b_0$ and $a_0$ are positive constants. Determine the average velocity $\bar{v}(t)$ at time $t$.

Determine the lines of current $y = y(x)$ and the acceleration $\vec{a}(x,y)$ for a stationary bidimensional flow described by the velocity field :
\begin{equation*} 
{\bf v} = (\frac{{v_0 }}{l})(x\vec e_x  - y\vec e_y)~.
\end{equation*}

Considering the set of triangles previously calculated, estimate the fraction of triangles of configurations  {+,+,+}
 ,  {−,−,−}
 ,  {+,+,−}
 , and  {+,−,−}
 . What fraction of triangles are "balanced" according to structural balance theory?
